    Compute covariance matrix for a Gaussian process

    compute_cov_matrix(points, cov_func, ...)

    Arguments

    points

    A data frame with n rows and d columns.

    cov_func

    A covariance model. Options are white_noise, brownian_motion, exponential, and matern_model. For all functions (except for brownian_motion), one can provide sig2. Also, for the exponential model, one has to provide the parameter beta, and for the matern_model model, the parameters nu and beta. See https://avramaral.github.io/STAT294/rpack.html for more details.

    ...

    Additional parameters. See above.

    Value

    An n by n covariance matrix.
